''Spud'' by [[John van de Ruit]] (2008)\n*''Sebastian Darke: Prince of Fools'' by [[Philip Caveney]] (2008)\n*''Spud: The Madness Continues'' by [[John van de Ruit]] (2009)\n*''[[The War of the Worlds]]'' by [[H. G. Wells]] (2012)\n\n=== Video games ===\n\n* ''[[James Bond 007: Nightfire]]'' (2002) as [[James Bond (literary character)|James Bond]]\n* [[Eragon (video game)|''Eragon'']] (2006) as Brom\n\n==Discography==\n\n* 1982: \"Charades\" on the ''[[Grease 2 (soundtrack)|Grease 2]]'' soundtrack (as Michael Carrington)\n* 1982: \"(Love Will) Turn Back the Hands of Time\" with [[Michelle Pfeiffer]] on the ''[[Grease 2 (soundtrack)|Grease 2]]'' soundtrack\n* 1982: \"Who's That Guy?\" with Cast on the ''[[Grease 2 (soundtrack)|Grease 2]]'' soundtrack\n* 1982: \"Reproduction\" with Cast on the ''[[Grease 2 (soundtrack)|Grease 2]]'' soundtrack\n* 1982: \"Rock-A-Hula-Luau (Summer is Coming)\" with Cast on the ''[[Grease 2 (soundtrack)|Grease 2]]'' soundtrack\n* 1982: \"We'll Be Together\" with Cast on the ''[[Grease 2 (soundtrack)|Grease 2]]'' soundtrack\n* 1995: \"Say No More (Mon Amore)\" in Alan Moyle's ''[[Empire Records]]'' (as Rex Manning)\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n\n* [[Theater World Award]] (1979) for his performance in ''Class Enemy'' ([[Players Theatre]], [[West Village]], New York City).<ref name=\"broadway\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|0001028}}\n* {{IBDB name}}\n* {{iobdb name|14561}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Caulfield, Maxwell}}\n[[Category:1959 births]]\n[[Category:English people of Scottish descent]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American male film actors]]\n[[Category:American male musical theatre actors]]\n[[Category:American male soap opera actors]]\n[[Category:American male stage actors]]\n[[Category:American male television actors]]\n[[Category:American male voice actors]]\n[[Category:English expatriates in the United States]]\n[[Category:English male film actors]]\n[[Category:English male musical theatre actors]]\n[[Category:English male soap opera actors]]\n[[Category:English male stage actors]]\n[[Category:English male television actors]]\n[[Category:English male voice actors]]\n[[Category:20th-century English male actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century English male actors]]\n[[Category:People with acquired American citizenship]]\n[[Category:People from Belper]]\n", "name_user": "Moe1810", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eStage credits", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maxwell_Caulfield"}
{"title_page": "Lal (actor)", "text_new": "{{short description|Indian actor and director}}\n{{EngvarB|date=August 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name        = Lal\n| image       = Lal (actor) BNC.jpg\n| caption     = \n| birth_name  = M. P. Michael\n| birth_date  = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1958|12|02}}\n| birth_place = [[Kochi, India|Kochi]], [[Kerala]], India\n| nationality = [[India]]n\n| occupation  = {{hlist|[[Actor]]|[[Film director |Director]]|[[Screenwriter]]|[[Film producer|Producer]]|[[Film distributor|Distributor]]}}\n| yearsactive = 1984 \u2013 present\n| spouse      = Nancy Lal\n| children    = [[Lal Jr.]]<br>Monica Lal\n| awards      = [[National Film Awards]]<br>[[Kerala State Film Awards]]\n}}\n\n'''M. P. Michael''' (born 2 December 1958), better known by his [[stage name]] '''Lal''', is an Indian actor, screenwriter, film director, producer, and distributor, who predominantly works in [[Malayalam cinema]] and has also appeared in Tamil and Telugu films. Lal has won one [[National Film Award \u2013 Special Mention (feature film)|National Film Award \u2013 Special Mention]] for acting (in 2012), two [[Kerala State Film Award for Best Actor]] (in 2008 and 2013) and a [[Filmfare Award for Best Actor \u2013 Malayalam]] (in 2008).\n\n==Early life==\nLal was born as Michael to M. A. Paul and Philomina. He is a devout member of the Roman Catholic [[Latin Rite ]] [[Archdiocese of Verapoly]], [[Ernakulam]]. His father M. A. Paul was a famous [[Tabla|tabla player]]. His brother Alex Paul is a famous [[music composer]] in the [[Malayalam film industry]] and his son [[Jean Paul Lal|Jean]] is a movie director in the same industry.\n\n==Career==\nHe started his career as a mimicry artist in [[Kalabhavan]], along with his childhood friend [[Siddique (director)|Siddique]], who would later team up as '''Siddique-Lal''' to make many films.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cochinkalabhavan.com/contribution.html|title=Cochin Kalabhavan|website=www.cochinkalabhavan.com}}</ref> Lal and Siddique began their film career working as [[assistant director]]s to [[Fazil (director)|Fazil]] in ''[[Nokkethadhoorathu Kannum Nattu]]''.<ref>{{cite news |title=Kunchacko's Udaya Studio being razed |url=https://english.manoramaonline.com/entertainment/entertainment-news/2019/05/04/udaya-malayalam-movies-famed-studio-razed.html |accessdate=24 July 2019 |work=[[Malayala Manorama]] |date=4 May 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"Mathrubhumi_1\"/>\n\nAfter that, both decided to part ways as a director pair and Lal turned producer with the Siddique-directed [[Mammootty]]-starrer ''[[Hitler (1996 film)|Hitler]]''.<ref name=\"Mathrubhumi_1\"/> Lal debuted in acting with a villain role as Paniyan in [[Suresh Gopi]]-starrer ''[[Kaliyattam]]'', directed by [[Jayaraj]]. ''Kaliyattam'' was a new take on ''[[Othello]]'', where Lal played Paniyan, the character standing for [[Iago]]. He runs a film post-production company named as Lal Media Arts, [[Kochi]]. For his performance in the 2012 film ''[[Ozhimuri]]'', he won the [[National Film Award \u2013 Special Mention (feature film)|National Film Award \u2013 Special Mention]].<ref>{{cite news|title=A Great year for Malayalam cinema, say National award winners|url=http://www.mathrubhumi.com/english/movies/malayalam/134554/|accessdate=24 June 2013|newspaper=mathrubhumi.com|date=25 March 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130327105403/http://www.mathrubhumi.com/english/movies/malayalam/134554/|archive-date=27 March 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nLal is married to Nancy and they have two children\u2014[[Jean Paul Lal]] and Monica Lal. Jean Paul is a film director.\n\n==Awards==\n;[[National Film Awards]]\n*2012: [[National Film Award \u2013 Special Mention (feature film)|Special Mention for Acting]] \u2013 ''[[Ozhimuri]]''\n\n;[[Kerala State Film Awards]]\n*1991: [[Kerala State Film Award for Best Film with Popular Appeal and Aesthetic Value|Best Film with Popular Appeal and Aesthetic Value]] - ''[[Godfather (1991 film)|Godfather]]''\n*2008: [[Kerala State Film Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]] \u2013 ''[[Thalappavu]]''\n*2013: [[Kerala State Film Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]] \u2013 ''[[Ayaal]]'', ''[[Zachariayude Garbhinikal]]''\n\n;[[Filmfare Awards South]]\n*2008: [[Filmfare Award for Best Actor \u2013 Malayalam|Best Actor \u2013 Malayalam]] - ''[[Thalappavu]]''\n\n;[[Asianet Film Awards]]\n*2010: Best Director \u2013 ''[[In Ghost House Inn]]''\n\n==Filmography==\n===Actor===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+Malayalam films\n! Year !! Title !! Role \n!Notes\n|-\n|1994 || ''[[Manathe Kottaram]]'' ||Guest at the wedding \n|Cameo Appearance\n|-\n|1997 || ''[[Kaliyattam]]'' || Paniyan / Iago \n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" |1998\n|''[[Kanmadam]]''|| Johny\n|\n|-\n|''[[Punjabi House]]''|| Sikkandar Singh\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Daya (film)|Daya]]'' || Kombanali \n|\n|-\n|''[[Ormacheppu]] ''|| Jeevan\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |1999 ||''[[Friends (1999 film)|Friends]]''|| Man at the park\n|Cameo Appearance\n|-\n| ''[[Chandranudikkunna Dikhil]]'' || Parthan \n|\n|-\n|''Jananaayakan''|| Misra\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|2000  || ''[[Mazha]]'' || Chandran \n|\n|-\n| ''[[Arayannangalude Veedu]]'' || Sukumaran \n|\n|-\n| ''[[Nakshathragal Parayathirunnathu]]'' || Gowrishankar \n|\n|-\n| ''[[Thenkasipattanam]]'' || Dasappan \n|\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|2001 || ''Ee Nadu Ennalevare'' || Plappalli Sreedharan\n|\n|-\n|''[[Randam Bhavam]]''|| Mohammad Ibrahim\n|\n|-\n|''Unnathangalil''|| Shiva\n|\n|-\n| ''[[One Man Show (film)|One Man Show]]'' || Hari Narayanan \n|\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"| 2002  || ''Ente Hridayathinte Udama'' || Pavitran \n|\n|-\n| ''[[Kannaki (film)|Kannaki]]'' || Manikyan \n|\n|-\n|''Krishna Gopalakrishna''|| Swamiji\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Kalyanaraman (2002 film)|Kalyanaraman]]'' || Thekkedathu Achuthankutty\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" |2003\n|''Uthara''|| Ambi\n|\n|-\n| ''Sinkari Bolona'' ||Deva Sharma \n|\n|-\n| ''[[Anyar]]''|| Raghavan\n|\n|-\n|''[[Pulival Kalyanam]]''|| Karunan\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |2004\n| ''[[Chathikkatha Chanthu]]'' || Film Director Ravikumar\n|\n|-\n|''[[Ee Snehatheerathu]]''|| Chinnappa Gounder\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Black (2004 film)|Black]]'' || Devin Carlos Padaveedan \n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |2005\n|''[[Thommanum Makkalum]]''|| Sathyan\n|\n|-\n| ''Banglavil Outha'' || Outha \n|\n|-\n|''[[Chanthupottu]]''|| Divakaran\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 2006  || ''[[The Don (2006 film)|The Don]]'' || Kasim Baba \n|\n|-\n| ''[[Pothan Vava]]'' ||As Himself\n|Cameo Appearance\n|-\n| ''[[Oruvan (2006 film)|Oruvan]]'' || Bharathan \n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |2007\n|''[[Panthaya Kozhi]]''|| Raghavan\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Time (2007 film)|Time]]'' || Dr. Srinivasa Iyengar \n|\n|-\n|''[[Rock N Roll]]''|| Issac\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" |2008\n|''[[Pachamarathanalil]]''||Mohammed Ali\n|\n|-\n|''[[Thalappavu]]''|| S. Raveendran Pillai\n|\n|-\n|''Aayudham''|| Swami Antony Williams\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Twenty:20 (film)|Twenty:20]]'' || Radhakrishnan\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\"|2009  ||''[[Thirunakkara Perumal]]'' ||\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"7\" |2010\n|''[[Aagathan]]''|| Major George Joseph\n|\n|-\n| ''[[April Fool (2010 film)|April Fool]]'' || Dr. Mohana Chandran \n|\n|-\n| ''[[Penpattanam]]'' || Inspector Antony \n|\n|-\n|''[[Anwar (2010 film)|Anwar]]''|| Babu Sait\n|\n|-\n|''[[Shikkar]]''|| \n|Cameo in a song\n|-\n| ''[[Best Actor (film)|Best Actor]]'' || Vandippetta Shaji \n|\n|-\n| ''[[Kandahar (2010 film)|Kandahar]]'' ||\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=\"5\"|2011  || ''[[Payyans]]'' || John Varghese \n|\n|-\n| ''[[Salt N' Pepper]]'' || Kalathipparampil Kalidasan \n|\n|-\n| ''[[Bombay March 12]]'' ||\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Doctor Love (film)|Doctor Love]]'' || \n|Cameo appearance\n|-\n| ''[[Vellaripravinte Changathi]]'' || As Himself \n|\n|-\n|rowspan=\"8\"|2012  || ''[[Father's Day (2012 film)|Father's Day]]'' ||\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Unnam]]'' || Sunny \n|\n|-\n|''[[Cobra (2012 film)|Cobra]]''|| Kari (Karimoorkhan) \n|\n|-\n| ''[[Ozhimuri]]'' || Thanupillai & Sivanpillai 